01:20:41.333 --> 01:20:43.028
Fellas, I gotta get out of here.

01:20:43.100 --> 01:20:45.762
You finish up this job here.

01:20:45.833 --> 01:20:47.960
Don't have too many beers
at lunch.

01:20:48.033 --> 01:20:51.434
- Yeah, okay.
- Make sure you quit by 4:00.

01:20:51.500 --> 01:20:54.060
Whoa!
All right. I'm fine.

01:20:56.600 --> 01:20:59.091
Have you seen this sunset
out here?

01:21:01.166 --> 01:21:04.932
Larry would love these rooftops,
you know?

01:21:05.000 --> 01:21:08.094
Did you see his eyes?

01:21:08.166 --> 01:21:13.194
They were beautiful.
Brown, with little flecks of green.

01:21:13.266 --> 01:21:15.860
Wasn't he nice?
He's really nice.

01:21:16.933 --> 01:21:20.528
How old do you think Giovanni is?
No more than 40?

01:21:20.600 --> 01:21:22.534
Come in!

01:21:29.666 --> 01:21:32.396
The stars will be iealous
of you tonight.

01:21:32.466 --> 01:21:34.229
You are a vision.

01:21:35.433 --> 01:21:39.233
Thanks. You certainly
know how to talk.

01:21:47.600 --> 01:21:51.263
By the way, l invite you all
on your last evening in Italy.

01:21:51.333 --> 01:21:53.563
A friend of mine has a yacht.
You can see it from the balcony.

01:21:53.633 --> 01:21:56.261
I told him I would bring
all my American friends tonight.

01:21:56.333 --> 01:21:58.460
So you must all come, hmm?

01:21:58.533 --> 01:22:01.764
Yeah, we'd love that.
Faith, you in?

01:22:01.833 --> 01:22:04.301
Okay. Ciao. Have fun.

01:22:08.300 --> 01:22:09.562
I'm sorry.

01:22:09.633 --> 01:22:13.194
In another life or parallel universe,
we would have loved that. Better?

01:22:13.266 --> 01:22:15.757
- I have to get ready.
- Okay. Sorry.

01:22:16.933 --> 01:22:18.764
Wait, wait. Sorry.

01:22:20.133 --> 01:22:21.862
- Here.
- What is it?

01:22:21.933 --> 01:22:23.867
You'll see.

01:22:26.133 --> 01:22:28.863
- Shoes!
- Yeah.

01:22:28.933 --> 01:22:32.664
They're bone, a good color
for a date with destiny.

01:22:32.733 --> 01:22:35.600
It should be-- Don't worry
about those European sizes.

01:22:35.666 --> 01:22:38.226
It's perfect.
It should tit like a glove.

01:22:38.300 --> 01:22:40.962
- They do.
- Yeah?

01:22:41.033 --> 01:22:42.466
Good.

01:22:47.666 --> 01:22:50.601
Could you hand me my dress?
It's over on the window--

01:22:57.466 --> 01:23:00.230
And my earrings?
Those little moon ones?

01:23:00.300 --> 01:23:02.530
Yeah.

01:23:02.600 --> 01:23:05.592
And could you get me
my little ankle--

01:23:07.800 --> 01:23:09.233
Thanks.

01:23:31.666 --> 01:23:35.329
Oh, you got the pictures back
from the place.

01:23:37.600 --> 01:23:41.934
This one of us is great.
Did you see that picture that...

01:23:52.166 --> 01:23:53.463
Oh, God.

01:23:58.399 --> 01:24:01.096
Oh, you look great.

01:24:02.666 --> 01:24:04.600
Thank you.

01:24:12.899 --> 01:24:17.769
I just... I want to thank you
for making all of this possible.

01:24:17.833 --> 01:24:20.063
Sure.
It's th e l east I couId do.

01:24:20.133 --> 01:24:23.159
I just hope you find
what you're looking for.

01:24:37.000 --> 01:24:38.092
Stop.

01:24:38.166 --> 01:24:40.691
Oh, Peter, stop.

01:24:40.766 --> 01:24:43.428
No matter what happens tonight,
I love you.

01:24:44.699 --> 01:24:47.430
- I have to go.
- Yeah.

01:24:47.500 --> 01:24:50.628
It's pumpkin time.

01:25:12.000 --> 01:25:13.433
Oh!

01:25:18.500 --> 01:25:21.833
Wow. You look just like a goddess.

01:25:21.899 --> 01:25:26.064
You really do.
I mean, it's... Whoa.

01:25:26.133 --> 01:25:27.395
A lot of steps.

01:25:47.966 --> 01:25:50.400
- Want some wine?
- Yes.

01:25:50.466 --> 01:25:53.026
Do you have a good house red?

01:25:53.100 --> 01:25:54.533
Cool.

01:25:56.666 --> 01:26:00.295
Now, I know you're gonna think
this sounds crazy...

01:26:00.366 --> 01:26:04.029
but I noticed you at the pool
even before we spoke.

01:26:04.966 --> 01:26:07.764
I could sense
a chemistry between us.

01:26:09.233 --> 01:26:12.430
- Really?
- Truly.

01:26:43.466 --> 01:26:45.730
So...

01:26:45.800 --> 01:26:48.792
you're probably wondering
why I asked you to dinner.

01:26:49.766 --> 01:26:53.600
No, not really.
It happens all the time.

01:26:56.733 --> 01:26:59.031
Right.

01:27:00.166 --> 01:27:02.100
What looks good?

01:27:03.366 --> 01:27:05.459
I think I'm gonna have the scampi.

01:27:05.533 --> 01:27:08.297
Oh, you like shrimp?
I like shrimp.

01:27:08.366 --> 01:27:11.096
Get out of town.
Come on.

01:27:11.166 --> 01:27:13.100
Put her there.

01:27:40.333 --> 01:27:43.268
0o you believe in destiny?

01:28:04.033 --> 01:28:05.967
It is written...

01:28:07.166 --> 01:28:08.428
on the stars.

01:28:52.833 --> 01:28:56.769
My son Kyle is in the third grade.
He's really the smart one.

01:28:56.833 --> 01:28:58.824
My other son is very...

01:28:58.899 --> 01:29:02.666
physical, I guess,
would be the term.

01:29:02.733 --> 01:29:05.861
You think I'm just
one of those men...

01:29:05.933 --> 01:29:09.061
who tries to seduce
every woman he meets.

01:29:09.133 --> 01:29:11.601
Oh, I know that's what you are.

01:29:13.366 --> 01:29:15.300
Does it matter?

01:29:26.366 --> 01:29:28.357
I've told you all about me.

01:29:28.433 --> 01:29:31.095
- I want to hear about you.
- All right.

01:29:31.166 --> 01:29:34.966
What kind of books do you like?
What music do you listen to?

01:29:35.033 --> 01:29:38.730
I like action films.

01:29:38.800 --> 01:29:42.167
I like Van Damme movies.

01:29:42.233 --> 01:29:45.293
I love martial art films.

01:30:01.399 --> 01:30:03.891
Really?
You don't like opera?

01:30:03.966 --> 01:30:05.627
I'm surprised to hear that.

01:30:09.699 --> 01:30:12.669
- Giovanni, I'm sorry.
- What?

01:30:12.733 --> 01:30:15.429
You're very kind and gentle,
and I'll never forget you...

01:30:15.500 --> 01:30:17.934
but I can't do this.

01:30:18.000 --> 01:30:19.092
I'm married.

01:30:28.100 --> 01:30:30.534
- That makes me uncomfortable.
- I'm sorry.

01:30:30.600 --> 01:30:32.966
- How bout that?
- Come on. Stop it.

01:30:33.033 --> 01:30:35.661
- Is this what you want?
- I said stop!

01:30:35.733 --> 01:30:37.792
- Okay.
- Stop it.

01:30:45.100 --> 01:30:47.295
I'll kill you!

01:30:47.366 --> 01:30:49.334
- You crossed the line, you jerk!
- You crossed the line.

01:30:49.399 --> 01:30:52.631
- You blew it from the get-go!
- I did you a favor.

01:30:52.699 --> 01:30:54.463
I said to turn her off
not molest her!

01:30:54.533 --> 01:30:57.024
I was improvising.

01:30:59.000 --> 01:31:02.561
Are you not Damon Bradley?

01:31:04.466 --> 01:31:07.560
No, I am not Damon Bradley.

01:31:07.633 --> 01:31:10.966
Look, I'm real...
Damn it!

01:31:12.199 --> 01:31:14.691
I'm really sorry.
You're very sweet.

01:31:14.766 --> 01:31:16.791
- I'm sorry it went this far.
- Shut up, Harry! You've done enough!

01:31:16.866 --> 01:31:20.233
- You shut up.
- So you're probably really upset.

01:31:20.300 --> 01:31:22.700
- Just be a little bit rational.
- Rational!

01:31:23.733 --> 01:31:26.429
Hit him!

01:31:26.500 --> 01:31:28.764
- Let it out.
- Stop it!

01:31:31.433 --> 01:31:34.800
Okay, what's with
the bald guy, huh?

01:31:34.866 --> 01:31:37.699
- Faith, I can explain!
- Great.

01:31:37.766 --> 01:31:39.529
Okay, slow down.

01:31:39.600 --> 01:31:41.033
Oh, God.

01:31:41.100 --> 01:31:43.034
Oh, dear. Oh, my.

01:31:45.466 --> 01:31:48.594
Faith, I was afraid
of losing you!

01:31:48.666 --> 01:31:50.031
Let's go.

01:31:50.100 --> 01:31:53.194
You are so ungrateful. Do you know
what kind of planning this took?

01:31:53.266 --> 01:31:57.100
This was a maior production.
I did it all for us!

01:31:57.166 --> 01:32:00.431
Thank you very much.
I hope you're very happy!

01:32:00.500 --> 01:32:03.094
I don't believe in anything anymore!

01:32:03.166 --> 01:32:06.067
I don't believe in the moon or stars
or the sun or destiny...

01:32:06.133 --> 01:32:08.397
or magic or men!

01:32:08.466 --> 01:32:12.562
Why won't you accept the fact that
I'll do anything to keep us together?

01:32:12.633 --> 01:32:14.567
You've outdone yourself!

01:32:15.933 --> 01:32:18.265
You're gonna miss me
when I'm gone.

01:32:18.333 --> 01:32:21.700
You're nuts about me!
We're made for each other!

01:32:32.899 --> 01:32:35.198
Haven't they ever heard
of escalators?

01:32:43.766 --> 01:32:47.497
You didn't mean what you said about not
believing in the stars and the moon?

01:32:47.566 --> 01:32:49.500
- You?
- I...

01:32:52.133 --> 01:32:54.067
I can't.

01:32:55.233 --> 01:32:57.167
I can't now.

01:32:59.133 --> 01:33:02.534
I'm sorry for dragging you here.

01:33:02.600 --> 01:33:05.501
No, don't say you're sorry...

01:33:05.566 --> 01:33:09.195
'cause this has been the best weekend
of my entire life.

01:33:15.699 --> 01:33:19.602
I guess sometimes life just doesn't
turn out the way we imagined it.

01:33:25.699 --> 01:33:27.634
Look at the stars.

01:33:27.699 --> 01:33:30.430
They come out every night.

01:33:32.066 --> 01:33:34.933
ro almost love a woman
and then lose her.

01:33:38.133 --> 01:33:40.067
Enjoy the pain.

01:33:41.666 --> 01:33:45.602
It's like losing at roulette.
There's that sweet sting.

01:33:50.699 --> 01:33:52.634
Oh, Jesus, Harry.

01:33:56.166 --> 01:33:58.100
There's only one woman...

01:33:59.233 --> 01:34:01.167
and she's gone.

01:34:10.699 --> 01:34:12.793
Are you all right?

01:34:13.800 --> 01:34:15.859
- Yes.
- Can I get you something?

01:34:15.933 --> 01:34:18.128
No, thank you.

01:34:18.199 --> 01:34:21.931
I just would like you
to send this very quickly.

01:34:23.233 --> 01:34:25.098
Yes.

01:34:30.066 --> 01:34:33.558
I'm calling off my wedding.

01:34:36.833 --> 01:34:38.562
Sorry.

01:34:46.966 --> 01:34:49.093
I'll send it immediately.

01:34:55.533 --> 01:34:56.966
Thanks.

01:35:15.266 --> 01:35:16.733
Just go.

01:35:39.433 --> 01:35:40.593
I'm sorry.

01:35:40.666 --> 01:35:42.793
I wanna...

01:35:42.866 --> 01:35:44.800
Come on. Let's go.

01:36:06.866 --> 01:36:09.300
Larry?
What are you doin' here?

01:36:11.600 --> 01:36:15.730
What am I doin' here?
What the hell are you doin' here?

01:36:16.766 --> 01:36:19.360
You came all the way here
just to ask me that?

01:36:21.233 --> 01:36:23.497
No, I...

01:36:23.566 --> 01:36:26.694
I came all the way here
to tell you...

01:36:26.766 --> 01:36:28.256
I love you and l...

01:36:29.399 --> 01:36:30.731
miss you.

01:36:32.800 --> 01:36:35.360
I've been miserable
without you, Katy.

01:36:35.433 --> 01:36:38.095
Oh, Larry, I've missed you too.

01:36:46.833 --> 01:36:48.300
You're gonna be okay?

01:36:48.366 --> 01:36:51.529
I'm gonna be okay.
I want you guys to have a great time.

01:36:51.600 --> 01:36:53.397
- Did you call Mom?
- Yeah.

01:36:53.466 --> 01:36:55.263
- 0id you calI Dwayne?
- Yeah.

01:36:55.333 --> 01:36:57.358
What'd they say?
What?

01:36:57.433 --> 01:36:59.833
Everybody is worried about you,
you understand?

01:36:59.899 --> 01:37:02.596
- I'm all right. Thanks.
- You got everything?

01:37:05.666 --> 01:37:08.191
Listen, what time is your flight?

01:37:08.266 --> 01:37:10.826
- You got your passport?
- Yeah.

01:37:10.899 --> 01:37:12.094
Your ticket?

01:37:44.300 --> 01:37:45.927
I'm Damon Bradley.

01:37:46.000 --> 01:37:48.400
You're Damon Bradley?

01:37:48.466 --> 01:37:50.934
I mean, off the Ouija board,
when we were kids.

01:37:51.000 --> 01:37:53.298
I made the whole thing up.
I was pushing the arrow.

01:37:53.366 --> 01:37:56.130
- I wanted to get to the next question.
- You made the whole thing up?

01:37:56.199 --> 01:37:59.863
- Damon Bradley never existed?
- He was a kid in Little League.

01:37:59.933 --> 01:38:02.424
- He was a real jerk.
- What about the fortune teller?

01:38:02.500 --> 01:38:04.798
- That fat gypsy woman?
- Don't say that.

01:38:04.866 --> 01:38:07.426
I slipped her two bucks.
The whole thing was a joke.

01:38:07.500 --> 01:38:10.469
Larry, this is bad.
You have to tell Faith.

01:38:10.533 --> 01:38:12.694
I am not going to tell Faith.
She'll never speak to me again.

01:38:12.766 --> 01:38:15.599
- She called off her whole wedding.
- Because she's in love.

01:38:15.666 --> 01:38:18.692
Why would she call off her wedding
if she was in love?

01:38:18.766 --> 01:38:20.631
Because it's not Dwayne.

01:38:20.699 --> 01:38:25.034
What do you mean?
Then who is she in love with?

01:38:29.133 --> 01:38:31.067
- Spanish?
- How'd you know that?

01:38:31.133 --> 01:38:33.829
It's very nice suede.
How much you pay for them?

01:38:33.899 --> 01:38:36.664
87.50, American.

01:38:36.733 --> 01:38:38.928
- Wow. Could've done better.
- Better?

01:38:39.000 --> 01:38:40.865
I'll give you a card.

01:39:05.833 --> 01:39:08.393
Passengers on TWA flight
to New York...

01:39:08.466 --> 01:39:11.264
prepare to board
at gate number ten.

01:39:17.500 --> 01:39:19.764
Alitalia nonstop flight
to Boston...

01:39:19.833 --> 01:39:22.859
is now boarding
at gate number 40.

01:39:24.666 --> 01:39:28.898
Mr. Damon Bradley, please come
to the information desk.

01:39:35.833 --> 01:39:38.461
I'll be in touch.

01:39:41.033 --> 01:39:42.967
Excuse me.

01:39:46.800 --> 01:39:49.268
Excuse me.

01:39:54.466 --> 01:39:56.593
- I'm Damon Bradley.
- Oh, yes.

01:39:56.666 --> 01:39:59.464
- You have a message for me?
- Yes, I have a message.

01:39:59.533 --> 01:40:03.128
Mademoiselle Plantard will meet you
directly at your hotel in Geneva.

01:40:03.199 --> 01:40:05.600
Ah, thank you very much.

01:40:19.399 --> 01:40:21.095
Shall we?

01:40:28.533 --> 01:40:30.228
I'm Peter. This is Faith.

01:40:31.866 --> 01:40:35.802
We're a bit strange. She's been
Iooking for you her whole life.

01:40:35.866 --> 01:40:38.061
Basically.

01:40:38.133 --> 01:40:42.297
As a matter of fact,
she thinks she wants to marry you.

01:40:42.366 --> 01:40:45.130
Yeah.
Are you married?

01:40:45.199 --> 01:40:47.600
- No.
- Oh, good. Whew.

01:40:47.666 --> 01:40:50.260
- Do you have a good job?
- Of course.

01:40:50.333 --> 01:40:52.324
- Who are you?
- I'm sorry. Peter, Faith.

01:40:52.399 --> 01:40:54.925
We're just friends.
He's available.

01:40:55.000 --> 01:40:56.695
This is good.

01:40:56.766 --> 01:40:59.234
She thinks that you two
are meant to be.

01:40:59.300 --> 01:41:01.234
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

01:41:01.300 --> 01:41:03.700
The only problem is me,
because I'm in love with her.

01:41:05.033 --> 01:41:07.467
I love her more
than she'll ever know.

01:41:07.533 --> 01:41:08.966
But...

01:41:10.600 --> 01:41:14.263
You're a lucky man.
You've got the right name.

01:41:19.399 --> 01:41:22.062
Good-bye, Faith.

01:41:22.133 --> 01:41:24.294
I hope you work it out.

01:41:26.833 --> 01:41:28.266
Hope we work what out?

01:41:34.399 --> 01:41:36.334
What's going on?

01:41:37.966 --> 01:41:39.263
He loves me.

01:41:40.300 --> 01:41:42.234
I can see that.

01:41:42.300 --> 01:41:44.495
The question is: Do you love him?

01:41:45.699 --> 01:41:46.792
What?

01:41:46.866 --> 01:41:49.198
I said, the question is:
Do you love him?

01:41:49.266 --> 01:41:51.530
What?

01:41:51.600 --> 01:41:54.364
0o you love him?

01:41:55.866 --> 01:41:59.267
- Last call for boarding.
- I do.

01:42:03.800 --> 01:42:05.927
I do.

01:42:11.100 --> 01:42:12.192
Good.

01:42:13.433 --> 01:42:16.095
I have a plane to Geneva
to catch...

01:42:16.166 --> 01:42:20.227
and you have a plane to catch.

01:42:29.000 --> 01:42:32.299
Is this the flight to Boston?
I have to get on that flight.

01:42:32.366 --> 01:42:34.891
- The flight is closed.
- Excuse me?

01:42:34.966 --> 01:42:38.299
You don't understand.
The man I love is on that plane.

01:42:38.366 --> 01:42:41.164
- Are you sure?
- Yes, I'm sure!

01:42:41.233 --> 01:42:44.100
Please, can you help me?
You understand.

01:42:44.166 --> 01:42:45.963
Don't you?

01:42:47.833 --> 01:42:50.768
Do you got a ticket?
This is to New York.

01:43:15.500 --> 01:43:16.592
Okay.

01:43:18.000 --> 01:43:20.525
Oh, my God!

01:43:42.466 --> 01:43:44.400
Thank you!

01:44:39.600 --> 01:44:41.534
Good luck!

